The paper deals with graph layout parameters, specifically cutwidth, and provides a new algorithmic approach for computing cutwidth. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to graph theory and algorithms. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with combinatorial aspects of graph layout parameters. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category as the paper deals with linear ordering of vertices in a graph. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper provides a new fixed-parameter algorithm for computing cutwidth. 

cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph layout parameters, which are relevant in game theory applications. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with complexity theory, but the algorithmic aspects of the paper could be relevant to this category.
